blueprint.label: Cybersyn Depot Hub
blueprint.description:
This will support up to 10 trains waiting for schedules and provide fuel to any Cybersyn trains that need it.

To change the fuel type, find the Fuel "Special" train and change where it picks up.  That will update the entire surface.

entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description:
Calculate the average number of items per chest.
Using only the first car because a short-train could leave it empty while later cars make the station think it has capacity.

entities.name: constant-combinator
entities.player_description:
The "request threshold" is relative to a full train.  A NEGATIVE number will allow partial trains with up to that amount empty.  A positive number will delay calling a train until more buffer space is free so not really any use for it.  

Or remove the two combinators to the left-side of the track and then the "request threshold" becomes an absolute amount.  Check the output of those combinators to know how much is in a full train; it's in items, not stacks.
